from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge
In [133]:
x_axis = np.linspace(0, 1, 200)
fig, axs = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 7), ncols=2)
axs[0].scatter(X, Y)

w = []
b = []

alphas = [0.0, 0.1, 1.0, 10.0, 100.0, 1000.0]

for alpha in alphas:
    reg = Ridge(alpha=alpha)
    reg.fit(X[:, None], Y)
    pred = reg.predict(x_axis[:, None])
    w.append(reg.coef_[0])
    b.append(reg.intercept_)
    axs[0].plot(x_axis, pred, label="alpha=" + str(alpha))

axs[0].legend()
axs[0].set_xlabel("x", size=15)
axs[0].set_ylabel("y", size=15)
axs[0].set_title("Ridge     ")
axs[1].plot(alphas, w, label="w")
axs[1].plot(alphas, b, label="b")
axs[1].set_xlabel("alpha", size=15)
axs[1].set_ylabel(" ", size=15)
axs[1].set_title("  w  b    ")
axs[1].set_xscale("symlog", linthresh=0.01)
axs[1].legend()
plt.show()

Вопрос 4 (2 балла)¶

, ? (, )

: $$Loss = \sum_{i=1}^{n} \left ( y_i - \sum_{i=1}^{2}x_{ij}w_j \right )^2$$

j: $$\frac{\partial Loss}{\partial w_j} = \sum_{i=1}^{n} 2\left (y_i - w_1 x_{i1} - w_2 x_{i2}\right ) x_{ij}$$

: $$\frac{\partial Loss}{\partial w_1} = \sum_{i=1}^{n} 2\left (y_i - w_1 x_{i1} - w_2 x_{i2}\right ) x_{i1}$$

$$\frac{\partial Loss}{\partial w_2} = \sum_{i=1}^{n} 2\left (y_i - w_1 x_{i1} - w_2 x_{i2}\right ) x_{i2}$$

:

$$\frac{\frac{\partial Loss}{\partial w_2}} {\frac{\partial Loss}{\partial w_1}} = \frac{x_2}{x_1} = const$$

, $l_2$ . , , , . $l_1$ . sklearn $l_1$ Lasso

Вопрос 5 (2 балла)¶

$l_1$ ? (, , ).

: $$Loss = \sum_{i=1}^{n} \left | y_i - \sum_{i=1}^{2}x_{ij}w_j \right | $$

j: $$\frac{\partial Loss}{\partial w_j} = \sum_{i=1}^{n} \left (y_i - w_1 x_{i1} - w_2 x_{i2}\right ) x_{ij}$$

: $$ y_i \geq \sum_{j=1}^2 x_{ij}w_j: \ \ \frac{\partial Loss}{\partial w_j} = \sum_{i=1}^{n} \left (y_i - w_1 x_{i1} - w_2 x_{i2}\right ) x_{ij}$$

$$y_i < \sum_{j=1}^2 x_{ij}w_j: \ \ \frac{\partial Loss}{\partial w_j} = - \sum_{i=1}^{n} \left (y_i - w_1 x_{i1} - w_2 x_{i2}\right ) x_{ij}$$

model_lasso = Pipeline([
    ("scaler", StandardScaler()),
    ("regr", Lasso())
])

model_ridge = Pipeline([
    ("scaler", StandardScaler()),
    ("regr", Ridge())
])

alphas = np.logspace(-10, 10, 30)

lasso_cv = GridSearchCV(
    model_lasso,
    cv=5,
    scoring="neg_root_mean_squared_error",
    param_grid = {"regr__alpha": alphas}
)

ridge_cv = GridSearchCV(
    model_ridge,
    cv=5,
    scoring="neg_root_mean_squared_error",
    param_grid = {"regr__alpha": alphas}
)

# Your code:

lasso_cv.fit(X_train, y_train)
